Your goal is to create a monitoring tool for Linux servers (mainly, but not limited to - Debian based). The tool should be as lightweight as possible, with smallest possible footprint on hardware resources. It should be standalone and self-contained, meaning that it should not need any additional software to store metrics like influx.

The tool should gather:
- CPU usage with all the components like iowait, irq, etc. for all cores and for individual ones
- Load average
- RAM usage with all the components like free, available, used, buffers and cache etc.
- SWAP
- Network (tx/rx in Mbps), connections, sockets, it should be possible to view for all interfaces and also view details of tcp, udp, other traffic separately and for ipv4 and ipv6
- Disks (utiization, transfers, disk space, file systems)
- clock/time sync
- entropy
- uptime
- processes (tasks, states etc.)
- users
- self cpu and memory usage
Feel free to add something if you think it could be useful and it's worth adding while we're at it

We want to gather the metrics each second, be able to view them via TUI and via Web UI.
TUI should be simple and focus on general idea of the current (live) hardware usage, while web ui should have the detailed graphs and history data.
Web UI should have the current/live cpu, ram/swap, lavg and network dl/up speed on top in form of gauge graphs with the value/unit inside, then below there should be all the detailed graphs with current and history data combined. Graphs should be updated live. There should be an option to pause and resume the stream as well as to choose the date/time window, with some presets like last 5 minutes, last 15 minutes, 30, last 1 hour, last 3 hours, last 6 hours, last 24 hours, last week. It should be possible to select a time window on the graph (selecting a time window from the inddividual graph should change the time window for all of them.

The web ui should have option to enable auth/login.

There should be tiers of data retention.
Per 1 second we want to keep the data up to 100MB of sotrage. Second tier will be 200MB - 1 minute. And the 3rd tier will be 5 minutes - another 200MB. It should be easy to adjust these settings in the config file.
